Note that $2^{3}=8$. Thus, we have $\displaystyle |2^{x}-4|=3$. This equation gives us two cases to consider: one where $2^{x}-4=3$, and another where $2^{x}-4=-3$. In the first case, $2^{x}=7$, so $x=\log_{2}{7}$. In the second case, $2^{x}=1$, so $x=\log_{2}{1}=\boxed{0}$. The product of these solutions is simply $(\log_2{7})(0)=0$. Therefore, our answer is $\boxed{0}$.

